    "patch":  "@@ -0,0 +1,83 @@\n+# RGE ‚Äî External-Engine Lessons (harvest ledger)\n+\n+\u003e **Purpose.** A capture backlog of patterns observed in comparable engines, each mapped to the RGE\n+\u003e locus it could pressure-test. Mirrors kariyer\u0027s \"automation for ideas\" (capture ‚Üí stage ‚Üí promote),\n+\u003e **adapted to RGE\u0027s architecture freeze**: design docs (`PLAN`/ADRs) and code change **only when a row\n+\u003e is `promoted`, and promotion requires demonstrated implementation pressure, not forecast**\n+\u003e (`PLAN` ¬ß0.6: post-v0.8 subsystems require ‚â•3 concrete reproducible failure scenarios). This file is a\n+\u003e **reporter / backlog, not a gate** ‚Äî it authorizes nothing. Its value is to pre-stage designs so that\n+\u003e when pressure arrives, we build faster and better-informed.\n+\n+## The five kernel pressures\n+\n+Every engine kernel faces recurring *pressures*; comparable engines are donors of *solutions* to them.\n+Harvested lessons are organized by which pressure they address (per the OpenClaw‚ÜîRGE analysis,\n+2026-06-09):\n+\n+1. **Composition** ‚Äî heterogeneous, content-varying object state, attached and queried generically.\n+2. **Declarative content** ‚Äî content expressible to tooling + runtime loaders without recompiles.\n+   *Nuance:* a **fixed-schema** data-driven format can precede composition; it is **scalable /\n+   heterogeneous** content that eventually forces composable objects.\n+3. **Subsystem boundaries** ‚Äî volatile/specialized services (physics, audio, importers, scripting)\n+   behind a contract, so backend detail does not contaminate the kernel.\n+4. **Execution-time** ‚Äî the sim-time model (fixed vs variable step; determinism). A **kernel-identity**\n+   choice, *not* secondary: it legitimately bifurcates on \"do you need deterministic\n+   editor/replay/netcode?\" (OpenClaw ‚Üí variable, playable single-player; RGE ‚Üí Fiedler fixed-step,\n+   deterministic editor/replay). Same pressure, different valid answer.\n+5. **Authority arbitration** *(multi-model engines only)* ‚Äî when two models describe the same world\n+   (RGE: ECS runtime state vs CAD operator-graph geometry, bridged by `EntityCadMap`), deciding which\n+   model **owns truth**. This is *semantic governance*, not plugin hygiene ‚Äî and RGE\u0027s self-named #1\n+   risk (semantic-authority fragmentation). **No single-model donor engine has a pattern for it** ‚Äî it\n+   is the column where RGE cannot borrow blindly.\n+\n+## Two-gate promotion (how a row graduates)\n+\n+```\n+captured ‚Üí mapped ‚Üí [Gate A: phase] ‚Üí staged ‚Üí [Gate B: pressure ¬ß0.6] ‚Üí promoted ‚Üí adopted / rejected / n-a\n+```\n+\n+- **Gate A ‚Äî Prepare (phase / roadmap trigger).** When the mapped RGE locus is ~1 phase from opening:\n+  mine 1‚Äì2 donor engines and draft a concrete design sketch **in this ledger** ‚Üí `staged`. Forecast-OK\n+  because it commits nothing (no code, no `PLAN`/ADR/type change) and is freely discardable.\n+- **Gate B ‚Äî Promote (pressure, ¬ß0.6).** Only ‚â•3 concrete reproducible failure scenarios / a real\n+  consumer graduate a `staged` row to `promoted` (ADR + `PLAN` update, build authorized). The phase\n+  trigger can **never** reach this alone.\n+\n+### Guardrails\n+\n+1. Staging commits nothing; a `staged` row with no pressure sits indefinitely or is discarded.\n+2. **Anti-sunk-cost:** a polished staged design is *not* a reason to build ‚Äî only pressure is.\n+3. No code prototypes on forecast (a prototype is substrate ‚Üí waits for Gate B).\n+4. One file, richer status column; **no new lint, no ADR-for-the-process, no parallel authority.**\n+5. Record deliberate divergences (`n-a`) so an external pattern cannot re-litigate a settled RGE\n+   decision.\n+\n+## Backlog\n+\n+| ID | Lesson | Donor | Pressure | RGE locus | Promotion gate | Risk if misapplied | Status |\n+|----|--------|-------|----------|-----------|----------------|--------------------|--------|\n+| LES-001 | Cooperative `Process` chains (state machine + child-promote-on-success) as an interim task primitive | OpenClaw `ProcessMgr` | execution-time | `kernel/job-system` (v0 vocabulary, no executor) | both ‚Äî Gate A: a consumer wants sequenced async work; Gate B: that consumer is real | cooperative scheduling can mask the need for a true parallel executor ‚Äî keep it explicitly interim | mapped |\n+| LES-002 | Double-buffered, ms-budgeted event drain (re-queue overflow) | OpenClaw `EventMgr::VUpdate` | subsystem boundaries | `kernel/events` | pressure-only ‚Äî needs evidence of queue overrun / backpressure | a central bus competes with RGE\u0027s typed channels + change-detection ‚Äî do not recentralize comms | captured |\n+| LES-003 | LRU cache + refcount reclaim (`MakeRoom` / `FreeOneResource`) | OpenClaw `ResourceCache` (+ Bevy/Godot residency) | declarative content | `kernel/asset-streaming` + `asset-view` (stubs, Phase 4) | both ‚Äî Gate A: Phase 4 nears; Gate B: a scene actually thrashes memory | OpenClaw\u0027s single-thread refcount reclaim ignores GPU residency + async ‚Äî do not copy its threading model | mapped |\n+| LES-004 | Real archetype buckets vs single catch-all (both engines hit the full-scan / AoS wall) | OpenClaw (hot-component caching) + Bevy (archetypes) | composition | `kernel/ecs` (single catch-all archetype, full-scan queries) | pressure-only ‚Äî needs an entity-count profile showing the cost | premature archetype migration adds complexity with no measured win ‚Äî wait for the profile | pressure-pending |\n+| LES-005 | Physics behind an interface (`IGamePhysics` Strategy fa√ßade) | OpenClaw | subsystem boundaries | `physics` plugin | n-a | RGE already does physics-as-Tier-2-plugin (rapier, snapshot-participating); a fa√ßade would be a *parallel* mechanism | n-a |\n+| LES-006 | *(two-model truth ownership: ECS runtime state vs CAD operator-graph geometry)* | **‚Äî no donor ‚Äî** | authority arbitration | `cad-projection` `EntityCadMap` | RGE-internal only ‚Äî no external pattern to stage | **cannot be borrowed:** no single-model engine solves two-model truth ownership; RGE must design this itself (semantic-authority fragmentation = stated #1 risk) | open |\n+\n+## Donor engines to harvest next\n+\n+Bevy (archetype ECS, scheduler, change-detection ‚Äî RGE\u0027s closest sibling), Godot (scene/resource model,\n+editor UX), Fyrox \u0026 Flax (Rust / C# editor engines), O3DE (Gem / component model), *Game Coding\n+Complete* (OpenClaw\u0027s parent). **Practice:** when a cavity nears Gate A, mine 1‚Äì2 donors for how they\n+solved *that specific pressure* ‚Üí capture rows ‚Üí let Gate B decide promotion.\n+\n+## Reporter (deferred)\n+\n+A `report` script (√Ý la kariyer\u0027s `ideas/report.mjs`) that prints status counts + flags `staged` rows\n+whose RGE locus is under active work ‚Äî **deferred until the ledger is big enough to earn one** (don\u0027t\n+build the tool on forecast; eat our own dogfood).\n+\n+---\n+\n+*Seeded 2026-06-09 from the OpenClaw ‚Üî RGE kernel comparison. History: the five-pressure frame was\n+synthesized across a Claude/Codex exchange under owner arbitration; `LES-005` is a recorded divergence,\n+`LES-006` is the no-donor authority-arbitration row.*"
